											</div>
					<div style="float:left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject:<a name="91251" href="http://www.ldonline.org/xarbb/topic/33430#91251">Re:  Physical Abuse from peer and verbal abuse from teacher
</a></strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>I am very sorry you and your son are going through this. I would start documenting every conversation you are having with any principals. I would also ask them to sign it. This might spark more accountability on their end. I agree, that stating you may have to go to the police if it is not handled, would also start to get the attention this needs. You may also want to consider contacting anyone above the principals, especially the special education directors. There numbers should be able to be found online, if not, request the principal give you the number. I hope this helps and your son gets the respect and dignity that he deserves. </p>
																				</div>
			</td>
